cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.CV, cs.DS 

The paper deals with efficient spatial temporal image search for multimedia streams, which involves handling large amounts of multimedia data with timestamps and geographical information. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Multimedia (cs.MM), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Databases (cs.DB), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Among these, cs.MM and cs.IR are the most likely categories, as they directly relate to multimedia data and search algorithms, respectively. cs.DB is also a likely category, as the paper proposes a novel index structure for efficient insertion and deletion of spatial temporal images. cs.CV and cs.DS are less likely categories, as they are not directly mentioned in the abstract, but they could still be relevant given the focus on visual relevance and algorithmic efficiency.
